						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, central shrine, Vaṭamūlēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 8: 979 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 12 sheep left incharge of the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> Śiṟupaḻuvūr by Rāmaṉ Kōviyār, the wife of Paḻuvēṭṭaraiyar Vikramādityar for providing a <hi rend="italic">piḍi</hi> of ghee to God Mahādēva of Tiruvālanduṟai in Śiṟupaḻuvūr probably for burning a lamp.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 212.</p>						

						</summary>
